<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=551&amp;p=4465#p4465</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=551&amp;p=4465#p4465"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[28pin 1 or 2 meg eproms?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=551&amp;p=4465#p4465"><![CDATA[
NES games did use 128 Kilobyte (1 Megabit) 28-pin Program ROMs at times, but they are not common by any means.  No NES game ever used a 256 Kilobyte (2 Megabyte) 28-pin ROM.  I assume Nintendo used these odd ROMs during chip shortages or when they could get a good deal on them.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=58">Great Hierophant</a> — Sun Sep 11, 2005 2:31 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
